E.10 verify (2026-05-13):

Full authoring lifecycle on production: CREATE draft → no triggers
registered → dry-run captures intent → operator revises → second dry-run
captures revised intent → activate → Composio trigger registered → real
sheet-row event → real cloud_run (dry_run=false) → real SMS to operator
phone → cleanup.

Note: Composio's polling worker was backlogged during the verify window
and never fired its own poll against the registered trigger. To close
the loop on the post-Composio chain (signature verification → router →
trigger_event_log → cloud_runs → SQS → worker → SMS), I synthesized
a webhook payload with the real shared HMAC secret and POSTed it
directly to /webhooks/composio. Composio's polling reliability is their
service's responsibility; our trigger registration code is correct
(verified by the trigger appearing in Composio's /trigger_instances/
active with the right config, and by Composio API tools — including
GOOGLESHEETS_BATCH_UPDATE — successfully reaching the same sheet via
the same connected_account_id). D.9 already demonstrated end-to-end
Composio→our-webhook delivery live.

