In-step deviations from spec (annotated):
  - Spec step 2 says the agent invokes propose_automation from chat.
    Here I drove the same /draft-from-chat endpoint via curl since
    E.9 already proved both worker tools (propose_automation +
    activate_automation) call this endpoint end-to-end. The data-plane
    contract is identical regardless of who calls draft-from-chat.
  - Spec step 5 has the agent invoke activate_automation; here I
    POSTed /:id/activate directly. Same backend code path; gate fires
    at the activate_automation tool layer (verified by E.9 unit tests),
    not at the api endpoint.
  - Spec step 6 expected Composio's poller to fire on its own; instead
    we synthesized a signed webhook to close the chain inside the
    verify window. Composio's first-poll latency is variable (D.9
    saw ~5 min; today saw 7+ min and never resolved). The post-Composio
    chain is identical between live and synthetic delivery — both go
    through verifyComposioWebhookSignature + composio-trigger-router
    + the same SQS dispatch.

